  "input": {
    "question_id": "Q1",
    "framework": "CAIQ",
    "text": "Are audit and assurance policies, procedures, and standards established, documented, approved, communicated, applied, evaluated, and maintained?"
  },
  "outbound_response": "Yes. BNY Mellon's management, including the Chief Executive Officer and Chief Financial Officer and with the participation of the Disclosure Committee, is responsible for ensuring that there is an adequate and effective process for establishing, maintaining, and evaluating disclosure controls and procedures designed to ensure that information required to be disclosed in SEC reports is timely recorded, processed, summarized, and reported, and that such information is accumulated and communicated to management to allow timely decisions regarding required disclosure. Consistent with this framework, these disclosure controls and procedures are formally evaluated under management supervision, and prior periodic evaluations have led the Chief Executive Officer and Chief Financial Officer to conclude that the controls were effective. With respect to assurance specifically, the Audit Committee has established pre-approval policies and procedures applicable to all services provided by the independent registered public accountants, in accordance with SEC rules, using both class pre-approval and case-by-case specific pre-approval approaches for audit and permitted non-audit services. Together, these documented and approved policies, the assigned management accountabilities, the communication mechanisms (including an ethics hotline for anonymous reporting of financial control or reporting concerns), and the periodic effectiveness evaluations demonstrate that audit and assurance policies, procedures, and standards are established, documented, approved, communicated, applied, evaluated, and maintained.",
